content: The game is beautiful, and the story had me engaged. The gameplay relying so heavily on rng to get the correct power up is frustrating and ruins the fun though. If you could swap endlessly it would be merely annoying, but since you can swap only once the game feels more like a slot machine than an endless runner. Limiting my actions in this way is frustrating without adding anything to the game, in my opinion.
Super cute, really creative and well done! I love the art and music and story. Highly recommend.
beautiful art and story, but i just hate the gameplay, its so enraging and boring
I really was bummed that you had to buy each individual jump but learned quickly that you mushrooms quick.I really like this game!

Cheerful concept and aesthetic with a charming, casual main game that is unfortunately stained by an annoying RNG mechanic that essentially turns the whole thing into a slot machine. There's nothing to learn from your losses oh, and when you finally win it feels hollow.

Save data keeps disappearing!! I wish I could give this game 5 stars - it's sweet, has charm and is aesthetically pleasing. But every time I leave my phone on sleep for more than a few hours my saved data disappears. Maybe not a problem if you can finish this whole game without a break.

The visuals and music are phenomenal! The world that it's built in is amazing and feels magical. It really gave me the sense to explore and learn more about it BUT the gameplay is the unique thing here, it's definitely not for everyone for sure and it relies a lot on RNG. If you're a patient person and accept the fact the game requires pure luck to win at times then yes this game is worth paying for. I'm not a fan of the game mechanics myself but the beautiful atmosphere makes up for it.

The art and quirky storyline is exactly my kind of thing but the swapping out random items and buying items and doing that on top of timing their use is just too much micromanagement for me. More frustrating then enjoyable. Ended up stopping playing.

The best pixel game ever i played. this game have fun story, and the gameplay is fantastic. the pixel art too cool for me, i'm very glad to find this game. i guess this game is not fun from the pictures, but when i playing this game, i changes my mind. thanks for creating this game.

It's a pretty sweet game, and the more you play it, the better it gets. It has a decent pacing and good progression. The story also manages to stay interesting ( up to where I played ), and the ost is just immersive enough to be considered good too. There's also a very "dark", but subtle tone to it, which just adds to the experience, but that would definitely made me spooked af if I had played this a few years ago when I was younger. Nice game, actually 10/10

Looks great however I found it annoying to play, tried to swap skills but it mostly doesn't work, then you die, apparently you have to sometimes swipe back but that only ends up opening up my phone menu, needs the controls changing quick. Wanted to like the game, sorry.
Cute game, and story, but it keeps crashing in the third scene during the xylophone part
This game is fantastic

Love the design! Love the gameplay & the extra tid-bits it trows at the player throughout the game! Nothing bad to say here, just a really cool, unique, clever game. I guess one little caviat would be that a major part of the gameplay includes swiping around the side of the phone screen which is a gesture used in Android, so it can result in accidental closing of the game.

In the beginning you don't warm to it. You feel it's clunky and poorly developed. You don't understand the point. But the further it gets on the more used to it you get, the more the universe builds, the more it reveals itself; you get used to the gameplay methods and can't put it down. It's amazing. I love it. It never stops surprising me. Really not a one trick pony, this game. It's beautiful.

Cute art design, but gameplay is lacking. You have to rapidly use one of various tools or power-ups to survive obstacles. These are limited in quantity, and your run only lasts as long as your power-ups. You only have 3 slots, but there are more than 3 power-ups. If the wrong ones are up, you fail. The types are placed randomly in the 3 slots. Swiping to change to another power-up is too slow and often fails, wasting your power-up. Runs are very short ... Is this a new "Endfull runner" genre?

Unique, but underbalanced... you either have to be good at the whole last second timing thing, or you eventually get to a point where you can't progress...those dang piano tile games are easier....after so long, you will spend as much coinage on powerups, which the game runs on, as you will make per run....some tasks require you to crash and HOPE you did so in the correct spot...gets old quick...

Great game but controls sick a bit. The controls and a bit hit and miss. I'll swipe to change item and nothing happens. Other times I'll press the jump item and nothing happens. Also, this is a 2d game. Why does is sick up battery and make my phone warm?
Pretty great game,glad i bought it.the controls are even better when you have a controller.just wished the power ups could randomize on the triggers.

An amazing pixel art forest, characters, and simple but fun game mechanics. Awesome storyline with upgrades, clothing variations, driving boosts and mushroom currency easily collected each ride. All in all great game!
It's incredibly frustrating but SO SO GOOD. Everytime I fail makes me annoyed, but at the same time I can't wait to repair the cars and go at it again. It's just really beautiful and fun!

It's been a bumper year for indie games and this stands out as one of the best and most unique. Yes, it can be frustrating and confusing at times, but it's also one of the most beautiful, individual and well-written games I've ever played. For every time I was frustrated there was a line of dialogue to make me smile, a clever new gameplay element or just some small detail that showed how much love was put into this. For me this is a keeper. Don't understand the ending though.
This game is not for everyone. Game play is annoying. BUT I'll always feel l like it's my fault where I fail.

What a beautiful and cute game. The story is cute, the games hand animated pixelated graphics are fabulous, and the mechanics are simple yet challenging. Think of a well made, death-road-to-canada style incremental game. Like those jetpack games that you upgrade to go further and further, except this is well made with a sweet story. Its level style game is perfect for on the go play, but its story will keep you playing. Do yourself a favor and drop 5 dollars on this game. You wont regret it.
Cute
This is just not the kind of game I like. It's cute, the gameplay is mostly pleasant, but you depend on random chance to pass obstacles. Which is yuck.
So I finished an objective last night only to return to the game and find that it saved none of my progress...darn.
Great game controls to swap interferes with my home button otherwise 5 stars
It is so good the graphics and the boss I have to run from the adventure to see summer it is cool and the things that happen in the adventure that you not believe happened
At first it seems like all other endless runners...but it is so much more. I love it.
sucks

Surprisingly good, with good surprises. The gameplay itself is fun and interesting.. The challenges to complete each level are appropriately challenging. And then there are the bonus challenges within each level! I loved this game.
Game won't even load. Tried going in it twice and just made my phone restart, rating 1 star. Fix this issue and I'll up my rating

Played it a bit just to get erased. I got all first upgrades and now that I get back on my profile is still there but nothing got saved. I don't think I'll be continuing since loosing a few hours of progress just plain sucks
The game is truly a blast to play and i would be more then happy to give 5 stars if it was to give a bit more explanation of things like the bell what is it whats it for how is it used....etc.
Nice art but game's mechanics is annoying, unplayable and frustrating.
Very nice looking but the gameplay and controls are incredibly frustrating. Every single move you make uses a consumable item that you have to manually repurchase every time you die.
I love it, its not overly complicated but the story moves forward at such a pace as to keep the game entertaining!

I had downloaded this game a little while ago and forgotten that I had refunded it right away due to the fact that it would not load. I just purchased it again (I forgot the previous situation) ... I'm having the same issue... it starts up and is stuck on the screen of the shadow driving. I've never even seen a main menu. I LOVE noodlecake studio's other games and I am constantly purchasing and downloading games from Google play. I am unable to refund it. I would rather it work than a refund.
Excruciatingly annoying.
Fun
The art is great. The story is great. My only problem is I suck at this game. But the devs did a great job. Worth the money

Beautiful game and story but doesn't save your progress. Resets every time I exit. Edit: Even though the game is linked to my play store account and a save slot selected, it doesn't save my progress when I clear areas. Save slots are blank when I exit the game and open it later.
replyContent: Hello. Thank you for playing Summer Catchers. I'm really sorry to hear that you are experiencing issues with our game. Can you explain your issues in a little more detail to us by sending an e-mail to summercatchers@gmail.com? Thank you!

content: Was strugling a bit in the beginning. But once you get over first boss and find out hows the game works it will get more interesting and involving. I love that we still having devs trying to make good games instead of money grinding trash.
I love the game but I wish it was easier to swipe the tools to change.
Looks really good, but gets horribly annoying to play after the first world. It's honestly rage inducing, and not worth any price tag at all.

Cute graphics with nice music, bad gameplay. Swiping through your abilities while obstacles are coming at you (while they are being partially obscured by the selection interface) is frustrating and just plain stupid. The whole random selection system of powerups in your inventory at any given time is also probably the most annoying mechanic I have ever seen in an endless runner!
This game is a beautiful journey and forces you to experience it's world and not rush through it :)
Great game, but it really needs a left hand mode.
It's dark fun
Fun at first but I reached a part where you are supposed to get bat guano and it is impossible. I stop and honk my horn like it says but the little circle never fills up. Very frustrating.
This is a fun, well crafted game with a lot beneath the surface. Worth spending your money on.
I would give 5 stars but it keeps crashing after the 2nd boss fight. I have emailed the developers twice now and nothing has been fixed.. I have not even recieved a reply.

Very great game! I like how it is an endless runner but it isnt at the same time, like it has progression. The little changes in gameplay such as puzzles and rhythm mini games was cool too. I loved the characters you encounter and I was always anxious to see what happened next.
Nice but boring after a couple of tries...

I have purchased the game because I am a huge fan of Alto's Adventure and Odyssey. I hate to say it but I am extremely disappointed. You're forced to get over obstacles with the help of the tools that appear in a RANDOM order, but you also have these tools' icons overlapping the actual view and can't see the obstacles themselves. It's a disaster. Lastly, the speed at which the vehicle is moving is so high, that a normal person with good reaction simply does not have enough time to make a choice.
Beautiful game, controls are a bit annoying though.
Great music and graphics. Anything from noodlecake is amazing, and this game is no different.
Loving the game and art style!

A really good game, with beautiful graphics. Definitely a great time killer. Currently having an issue on the xylophone part. My game crashes when I try to play it. If that gets fixed I would definitely give a 5 star.
replyContent: Hi there, Thanks for playing Summer Catchers! I'm sorry you are experiencing issues with the game. Can you explain you issues in a little more detail to us by sending us an e-mail to support+summercatchers@noodlecake.com? Thank you!

content: The game window would not resize and made it hard to see stuff

Выглядит отлично, звучит хорошо, но не дотягивает до Одиссеи. Геймплей скучный, не затягивает. Преодоление препятствий карточками, случайно получаемые из запаса - странное решение, наравне с необходимостью их докупать перед стартом. А их размещение на экране попросту перекрывает сами препятствия. Не стоит заявленной цены.
Great casual game.
It looks great, music isn't bad, it's just boring. It doesn't innovate auto runners, plus it seems silly to put the interface buttons on top of the incoming obstacles. Not really worth the price tag.
Nice simple game that gives you a slight challenge. The graphics, animation and atmosphere or the game is beautiful.
